snippet.title: Brandon Zarzyczny
snippet.description:
Hi, my name's Brandon, but you can call me Big Z. I absolutely love films, books, and video games, so I decided to talk about them for fun on YouTube. I put out weekly video reviews for movies, mostly focusing on new releases and any new Horror film I can get hands on. I also try to put out one larger review for each of my favorite authors every month. 

If you dig around in my back catalog of videos, I used to upload Rock Band DLC videos every Tuesday when the new DLC came out, and they're all still on my channel even though they don't serve much use anymore. More recently I've uploaded a bunch of videos of my dogs and video game glitches I've experienced. I also have a couple of videos of live bands and other random stuff. 

Thanks for checking out my page and/or my videos! :)

snippet.title: Toby DeMoss
snippet.description:
Howdy, folks!

If you're here, odds are you're young, bright, and ready to change the world for the better. 

Me too :) 

We‚Äôre who this channel is for.

How do we get there? I chat with smart, kind, passionate businesspeople who educate young folks on ethical, effective entrepreneurship. We will focus on becoming better men and women, fathers and mothers, neighbors and friends. We will grow in integrity, sincerity, and love. And all the while we will be living productive, historic, worthwhile lives. 

Yay :)

So if you're here for it, let me tell you what kind of stuff we'll cover:

1. Entrepreneurship (and how to become really, really good at it)
2. Collaboration (and the importance of relating well to people)
3. Personal Finance (and the joys of financial freedom and generosity)

This stuff gets me pumped. I hope you feel the same way!!!

Let‚Äôs grow as we go, yeah?

Cheers,

Toby DeMoss ü•Ç

snippet.title: A WELLSPRING OF THOUGHT
snippet.description:
Hello Friends,

I am Jeannette. I love God, people, and nature. And I am, in many ways, eclectic. Therefore, you may see a variety of topics covered on my channel.

For now, however, I am focusing on writing. I have published two books so far, and the rest are in my head waiting to come out.  

My primary purpose in creating content is to obey God and bless you. If I can encourage you to keep God first in your life and walk in your own calling, my efforts will be well worth it. 

Do you have a story to tell? Do you want to write a book or need help with a writing project? Check out my website, www.http://www.awellspringofthought.com for more information. I would love to help you get your thoughts and ideas into writing or refine and polish your existing work.

Blessings,

Jeannette

snippet.title: Shelley Noble
snippet.description:
I am the maker/director of Halfland, an original, frame-by-frame, folktale stop motion animation for all ages, known and loved by dozens. It's been in the making for 23 years so far. I will post clips of scenes here as they are completed. Meanwhile, you can see a documentary on the progress made in 2010, read a New York Times write up about the project in 2012, or keep up to date with daily progress right now at Halfland's Blogger blog with photos via below links.

Thank you for your interest.

Docu: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WV4-f1U1ROo
NYTimes article: http://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/20/movies/stop-motion-animation-goodnight-molly-halfland.html?_r=4&pagewanted=1
Project blog:  http://notesfromhalfland.blogspot.com/

snippet.title: Greco Archibald
snippet.description:
Yellow Rangers! Welcome to Archibald's Awkward life. Where I post random things that may or may not be relevant to the existence of the human race.

My false name is John Grec Archibald you can call me Grec. I live in a small city south of The Philippines which is in South East Asia (for those who doesn't know where it is). I am 20-ish years of age and a graduated in college with a degree of BS Hotel & Restaurant Management, I am currently unemployed for now because I am soul searching for my next job. Yes, I've previously worked at Starbucks, a Hotel, Casino and a Restaurant. I did great with my previous jobs (I think) and the people who I've worked with loved me because I'm a very considerate person, but those line of work aren't my thing.

I would have loved to go to college with courses in Fine Arts, Illustration & Animation or Film School or something to do with ART, unfortunately my parent can't afford to pay such expensive fees. They don't make ton

snippet.title: J.Pooser Animations
snippet.description:
Hello fellow members of YouTube and users,

My name is James or J. Pooser Animations, and I want to welcome you to my channel. I started this channel back in 2013 as a means to showcase my newly found hobby of stop motion animation.  Whenever I came home from school, this is what I was working on. Several months after I started, I gained a new skill that applied my artistic abilities. I grew very annoyed with the lack of paint applications that Hasbro put into their figures, so I decided to do something about it. I started painting and customizing my figures. I am no professional, I'm just looking to improve, entertain, and have fun along the way! Cheers and thanks for stopping by!

Here on this channel you will find stop motions, customs, and voice overs that are done by me.

Thank you for your support!

Follow me on Instagram
@j.pooseranimations

LIke me on Facebook
facebook.com/jpooseranimations

Follow me on Twitter
@JPooserAnimatns

Very nice of you to read my boring description! 
Since you are on this side of my channel I guess you want to know something more about me, heh? :3
Well, I'm a 17 year old girl from a tinie tiny little country in Europe called the Netherlands or Holland or whatever you prefer to call it. And that's about everything you need to know. 
Just kidding!
My name is Amy and I created this channel on the 7th of September, 2012. 
I come here to escape my personal life and share my creativity with the world. 
I might not be as creative as some people out there but I still enjoy making videos whenever I have time on my hands. 
Other than editing I enjoy horseriding and writing stories on Wattpad, you can find me there by my old username : XxElsaxSnowQueenxX

Previously known as: 
-HollyJSinclair Fan
-XxElsaxSnowQueenxX

I like to change my username :) Although I might stick with my current one, I quite like it.

Are you still here? Well, thanks for staying with me!

snippet.title: Nellie K. Adaba
snippet.description:
I love all types of music and play the piano.
I'm a French native speaker from  Brussels, Belgium (born in 1981). I moved to Maryland in 94, then to NY, Westchester County in 99. 

I obtained my Bachelors/Masters in Spanish (Cum Laude)  and with a Minor in Italian  from Iona College. I'm taking  translation courses at NYU to earn Certificates in Translation, and Interpreter and Translator Preparation Certification Training at International School of Linguists for thebigword (language service provider) . 

I speak French, English, Spanish, and Italian.
 I'm currently working as freelance translator (French, English, Spanish, some Italian) and consecutive interpreter  (French-Enlish and Spanish-English) for Language Service Companies and NGOs/nonprofits and aspiring writer/poet.

I'd like to travel all over the world.

snippet.title: Rick DuFer
snippet.description:

snippet.title: HighVoltage Shock
snippet.description: My name is Pat Myra, and welcome to Cinephile90. A show in which the primary topic is music, particularly descriptions of the some of the most underrated and overlooked rock acts out there (mostly those apart of the alternative, industrial, and nu-metal sub-genre) and personal reviews on their most accomplished releases that I own so far. Many of these bands have either long-since broken up after releasing two or three albums, have barely reached any charts, are still together but have fallen out of the public eye, or are fairly well-known but still barely get the credits they deserve. Some of these bands are relatively known for their contributions to several movie soundtracks, which is how I would recognize the title of the band whenever I purchase the album. I also occasionally discuss films for certain specials. Please subscribe to my channel and enjoy as I bring you my encyclopedic knowledge of music and films to the public.

snippet.title: Kerith Louisa Williams-Catton
snippet.description:
Welcome to my channel friends old & new, My name is Kerry & i live in Brisbane, Australia with my three daughters. The music i put on my channel is mainly Northern Soul, Girl Groups, Doo-Wop, Ska, Reggae & anything really takes my fancy. What you won,t find is Heavy Metal, Punk or New Wave music as it,s not my cup of tea, but each to their own i say " live & let live "
Hoping very much you find something to your taste, Thanks for dropping by. Have a great day, peace & love . KK
" Lets spread the love of music world wide "

MY RANT AT YT.
I and a lot of my friends and fellow uploaders feel that the DISLIKE TAB should be removed asap by YT, This causes a great deal of controversy and " BAD FEELING " There is NOTHING to be gained hitting the dislike tab as the uploader will have spent hours making the video for all to enjoy. Sorry but that,s my view. KK.

snippet.title: Gianbros Eleven
snippet.description:

My name is Gian Carlo. Gian, for short. I graduated with a degree in Nursing, and currently employed as a Registered Nurse in a hospital in Los Angeles. Outside of work, I am a son, a friend and a big DORK. I love hanging out with my friends and explore different things. I love food and I love taking pictures. I enjoy going to shows, concerts, live shows and fairs. Ever since I was a kid, I've had this interest in film. It is a hobby I've always enjoyed. I am willing to explore more techniques to improve the quality of my videos.

I welcome likes, subscribers, and definitely friends. 
Enjoy my random videos.

snippet.title: Red Static
snippet.description: If you're new to my channel I just want to say welcome. I have been making videos since 2010 and it's become one of my favorite things to do. I started off the same way most people do, just filming shit with my friends. The reason I started making videos was because back in high school my friends and I would sneak out late at night to drink beers we were somehow able to get a hold of and we didn't have any other source of light other than my phone. The flash would stay on only when the video was recording and I ended up filming some of the most outrageous and enjoyable times of my youth. Going back and watching the footage of me and my friends getting stupid as teenagers opened the door of video making for me and I chase that same level of enjoyment to this day. There might not be many videos on this channel and especially videos that involve my personal life, but I bring a camera or two whenever I go on an adventure and maybe later in this channel's life I'll start putting it here.

snippet.title: Drew Gars
snippet.description:
I am a struggling screenwriter and film producer.

I am liberal in my politics.

Controversially, I am an 80s snob. Why? It's because the 80s has been used so much in pop culture, it came to the point where I'm sick of it. Not to mention, it brings out the worse in 80s kids,  all they complain about what Hollywood does with 80s properties, talking shit about Michael Bay is just as cliche as nerds being hackers. I don't care what the film industy does with the 80s, I never grew up with these properties. I am especially tired of the whole "Ruin My Childhood" shit. Listen, if you let any remake or film adaption of an 80s property "ruin" your childhood, you never had a childhood worth holding onto. Stop playing the victim card whenever Michael Bay or other filmmakers does something with the 80s. It's irritating.

snippet.title: SoggyCow
snippet.description:
I joined Youtube when I was 16 on October 29th, 2006. Under the name "zoofreakz" (youtube.com/zoofreakz).
When I turned 20 I decided I wanted a less-weird name and made this new channel in 2010.
On July 23rd 2012 I finally decided to Vlog and make entertaining videos for people so one day my children will know who I was growing up.
At the age of 26, in 2016, I went under the persona "SoggyCow" (youtube.com/SoggyCow).
In mid 2019, I closed my channel when to launch a FREE SPEECH social network called GabHub.com.
That failed after Google's Login API shut me down. I was literally targeted and defeated with 800+ active users in 2 weeks. NEVER USE GOOGLE API LOGIN FOR YOUR WEBSITES, IT GIVES GOOGLE LICENSE TO TURN OFF YOUR LOGIN AND DELETED ALL OF YOUR USERS/CUSTOMERS!
Late 2020, I reopened my channel, which got unpartnered & demonetized cuz apparently comedy is "Hate Speech" on this new WokeTube.
I'm now the creative director for AgonyOnline.com and proudly lead a game dev team on Steam.

snippet.title: tony crawford

YouTube the Best thing Since TV  
50 + yrs a Music Lover & Still going Strong. 
It all started with a Request for Me to Listen to a Young Singers Song & Vocal, As they had no one to Listen to them,, So  I agreed.  Its been Non Stop Since & with Singers  from almost every Country.
I Love Vocals that are a Little different to others,   Hit the Play Button & Lets Listen then
  I'm a Trained Domestic Violence Volunteer, Ex Women's Refuge Volunteer,   Also had a Brief Spell with a Family Contact Center  Via the Courts, So the  Parents Could  Get To See There  Child/Children with Good Quality Time & in Safety,  After a family Breakup.  

   So Now its Music All the Way, 
 Younger Singers,, Please Subscribe,, So Other Singers can Find Your Chn, 
I use FB as a backup Chn.  If your Looking for New Singing Friends, I have Friends form all over the World.
If your New to my Chn  WELCOME, & To  All My Other Friends THANK YOU

snippet.title: G Callen
snippet.description: Despite having built up the skillset in various disciplines of racing, martial arts, firearms and tactics and firefighting I'm still given the excuse that I'm need more to be a stunt man. Having trained in actual shaolin, tai chi, and krav maga I know what it's like to take hits at FULL force and to recover from falls as high as 20 ft. without a damn harness because there are no harnesses in real life. I raced cars and motorcycles but it's not good enough yet little miss "under represented" can come in and get first dibs on the job without those experiences. I drove backwards during a valet gig and was subsequently fired as a result but a woman does the same thing and gets a career in stunt driving...

snippet.title: Reign J
snippet.description: This channel is an encouragement corner. We all have issues and think that we are in the world alone. YOU ARE NOT ALONE! This channel allows everyone to come together to ask things they are curious about, be themselves ask those embarrassing but most sought out answers to common questions you would otherwise be afraid or too shy to ask or discuss with anyone. We are going to be your best friend and we don't judge anyone for anything here only positivity and wisdom along with honesty and compassion for those who need it are welcomed here. Unconditional love can be given virtually and I can show you how its done :) Their are good people left in the world and this channel will reinvent the notion that everyone is bad or out to hurt you because that is definitely not the case. Join us with our weekly discussions and outlandish but fun behavior from time to time...It is what it is lol no looking back! God bless

snippet.title: Geek Legion of Doom
snippet.description:
Contact us on Geeklegionofdoom@gmail.com
Postal address is Leo Ridgway, Safestore , 100 StMary's road, Southampton , UK . SO14 0AL

Geek Legion of Doom is one of the UK's biggest independent 'genre' movie review channels .We specialize in the independent movie that may have escaped your notice. Our reviews are honest and is the reviwers genuine opinion. Our policy is to give fair, constructive feedback on movies and TV shows from zero budget to blockbusters.
The team is spearheaded by Leo who created the channel  . With regular reviews from other Youtubers such as Paul from Buckaroobanzai channel & Arran from Screenstars aswell as other guests

But that's not all
-  Top 10 Lists
- Geek Movie / Comic Con reports
- Cosplay interviews
- Celebrity interviews
- Blu-Ray , Funko Pop and other collectibles collection overviews and updates
- Unboxing videos
- Opinion pieces and news video 
- Movie reviews - Scored 1-10 ( 1 being terrible, 5 being average 10 being incredible )
-Trailers

snippet.title: Rubina Shiver
snippet.description:
Hi everybody, my name is Rubina and I'm a pro make up artist from Italy (Venetian region). My journey in the make up world started back in 2009 but only recently (2018) I graduated at the Crisam Professional Make Up Academy in Verona. 
My personal style is a melting pot of Goth, Steampunk and Celtic culture. In this channel you will find make up tutorials, uncommon objects hauls, plus size goth fashion and vlogs from my travels and experiences.
Since English is not my native language, I apologize in advance for the many mistakes I do, please be kind in the comment section, I appreciate corrections but don't be rude.

You can find me also on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/rubinashiver/
and Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/RubinaShiver/
My business mail is rubinashiver@libero.it

If you like watching my videos subscribe to keep updated on new fun things I do :)
I upload every friday at 12 pm Eastern time.

snippet.title: Galactic Human
snippet.description:
An explorer of ideas about astronomy, history and alternative narratives that I may or may not actually believe but which leads me to greater vistas of knowledge and truth.  

I also explore survivalism from a left libertarian perspective that opposes racist, anti-gay, violent, and fascist narratives.  I support prepping and communal survival if an when the power grid that sustains centralized and hierarchical civilization comes down.  I am not an anarcho-primitivist in that I believe in technology but technology should not be a force of domination by some humans over others.  I believe in decentralized democracy and egalitarianism, not rambo-esque machoism.  My definition of survivalism is about the survival of the democratic ideal of the Enlightenment if and when the current global monetary system, based on banks issuing debt currency, cannot sustain itself.  I also explore quantum physics, consciousness and reality from non-reductionist perspectives.

snippet.title: ericbazinga
snippet.description:
Hi, I'm Eric, and I upload things here sometimes. 

If you're wondering why I use an avatar in my videos instead of just pointing a camera at my face, I'm what's known as a Virtual YouTuber. Basically, I film entirely in VR using an avatar, which not only makes my content more unique (especially since male V-Tubers are apparently a rarity), but also allows me to appear on camera while keeping my IRL identity private. (I like keeping my online and personal lives separate, and I'm kinda shy.) However, I'll occasionally use IRL footage as well, with my face out of the shot and/or obscured. 

My content is mostly VR-related, but I make videos unrelated to VR sometimes as well cause I don't want to do just VR like other Virtual YouTubers (PHIA comes to mind). Instead, I'm just gonna upload whatever the fuck I wanna make. No schedule, but I do try to have a new video out at least every month or so. Unfortunately, sometimes life just gets in the way, y'know?

Anyway, thanks for stopping by!

Everything is interesting! ARTexplains looks deep into psychology, science and history for the crazy cool facts and stories that make you go "Bwuh?"

No topic is too outlandish! Psychological Fallacies, Mental Health, Anatomy, Optical Illusions, Neuroscience, The Lost Empire of Yam... Take a look! It's like an encyclopedia with all the boring pages torn out! The host of this channel has a ligament of the human body named after him thanks to his episode on Belly Buttons, some undirected Wikipedia vandalism, and a top-tier medical journal: "the Xander ligament."

And it's scholarly! Research and citations included in each educational video's description!

Channel banner + profile picture designed by Hunter Afia, Falling Box Studios: https://twitter.com/FallingBoxD
